    <note>Yu(1) Jushan [22815] His great great grandson, Lie [22819], is identified as a lineage kin (zuren) of Yu(1) Hao [22814], who was the 6th generation descendant of Chou(2) [22815], who moved to Hangzhou when he served in the administration of the kings of WuYue. Chronological logic (taking into consideration the dates of Hao's elder brothers, would make Jushan a grandson of Chou(2). Jushan and his son, Changling [22816], were both known as classicists (rujia) in Hangxian. See also documentation for great grandson, Kuan [22818]. Xianchun Linan zhi, 60.19b.</note>
